# Data Center Sustainability: PUE Optimization & ESG Strategy
**Operational Strategy for Energy Efficiency and Decarbonization**

---

## 🌍 Project Overview
As data centers account for ~2% of global electricity consumption, efficiency is no longer optional. This project evaluates the **Power Usage Effectiveness (PUE)** of the 30kW IT suite designed in previous modules and implements strategies to reduce carbon footprint and operational expenditure (OPEX).

---

## 📉 1. PUE Calculation (Baseline vs. Optimized)
**Formula:** $PUE = \frac{\text{Total Facility Power}}{\text{IT Equipment Power}}$

| Component | Baseline (kW) | Optimized (kW) | Improvement Logic |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **IT Load** | 30.0 | 30.0 | Constant |
| **Cooling Load** | 23.0 | 14.0 | Implement Variable Speed Fans (VFD) |
| **Lighting/Misc** | 2.0 | 1.0 | LED + Motion Sensors |
| **UPS Losses** | 3.0 | 1.5 | High-efficiency ECO-mode UPS |
| **Total Power** | **58.0 kW** | **46.5 kW** | -- |
| **PUE Score** | **1.93** | **1.55** | **19.6% Efficiency Gain** |

---

## ❄️ 2. Cooling Optimization Strategies
To reach a PUE of 1.55, the following "Value Engineering" steps were applied:
* **Airflow Management:** Transitioning from open-air cooling to **Cold Aisle Containment (CAC)** to eliminate hot-spots.
* **Set-point Adjustment:** Increasing the supply air temperature from 18°C to 22°C (within ASHRAE TC 9.9 "Recommended" range) to reduce chiller compressor work.
* **Blanking Panels:** Installing 1U/2U blanking panels in unused rack spaces to prevent hot air recirculation.

---

## 🔋 3. The "Green" Transition (ESG)
**Objective:** Aligning infrastructure with Net-Zero 2030 goals.

* **Renewable Integration:** Feasibility study for On-site Solar (Rooftop) or Power Purchase Agreements (PPAs) to offset 40% of daytime load.
* **Waste Heat Recovery:** Investigating the use of rack exhaust heat for building water pre-heating (Circular Economy).
* **Water Usage Effectiveness (WUE):** Transitioning to "Dry Cooling" or closed-loop systems to minimize water consumption in water-stressed regions like Bangalore.

